<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
      <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"/>
      <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
      <title>Responsive email</title>
      <style type="text/css">
          body{margin: 0; font-family: open sans;}
        h1{color: white;}

        .button{background-color:#00C39C;
          max-width:50px;
          padding: 3px 10px 3px 10px;
          border-radius: 4px;
          color: white;
          display:inline-block;
          margin-top:15px;
        }

        .title{
          margin-bottom:-10px;
          margin-top:10px;
        }

        a:link{text-decoration: none; color:white;}
        a:visited{text-decoration: none; color: white;}
        a:hover div{text-decoration:none; color: grey; opacity:0.8;}
        .divlink{max-width:40px;} 

      </style>
  </head>
  <body>

        <table border ="0" ellpadding = "0" align= "center" width = "100%">
          <tr>
            <td bgcolor ="#00C39C" style ="font-size:1; line-height: 1; padding 0 10px 0px 10px;" align="center">
              <h1>Welcome to Arima!</h1>
              <h5>Hi <%= @user.username %>, Thank you for signing up! Here are a few helpful tips before you go off on your own!</h5>
              </td>
          </tr>
          <table border ="0" ellpadding = "0" align= "center" width = "55%">
          <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px 10px 20px 10px;" >
              <div class ="title" style = "font-size: 20px; color:#00C39C;"><strong>Questions Pages</strong></div>
              <br />
              <div>
                Here you can find all the questions asked by users like you. You can view and answer the questions in both the featured page, or in specific categories. <em><strong> Gain points with each answered question!</strong></em>
              </div>
              <a class ="divlink" href="http://arima.io/categories"><div class="button"><strong> Go!</strong></div></a>
            </td>
        </tr>
          </table>
          <tr><td style="font-size: 0; line-height: 0;" height="0" bgcolor="#F9F9F9">&nbsp;</td></tr>
          <tr><td style="font-size: 0; line-height: 0;" height="20">&nbsp;</td></tr>
        <tr>
          <td>
            <table border = "0" cellpadding = "0" cellspacing = "0" align = "center" width ="55%">
              <tr>
                <td style ="padding: 10px 10px 20px 10px;">
                  <div class ="title" style = "font-size: 20px; color:#00C39C;"><strong>Leader Board</strong></div>
                  <br/>
                  <div>
                    This is where your points go! The more points you have, the more things you can unlock on Arima. Also, bragging rights.
                  </div>
                  <a href="http://arima.io/leaderboard"><div class="button"><strong>Go!</strong></div></a>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr><td style="font-size: 0; line-height: 0;" height="20">&nbsp;</td></tr>
            </table>
            <table border="0" cellpadding ="0" cellspacing="0" align = "center" width = "55%">
              <tr>
                <td style ="padding: 10px 10px 20px 10px;">
                  <div class ="title" style ="font-size: 20px; color:#00C39C;"><strong>Profile</strong></div>
                  <br/>
                  <div>
                    Your personal profile, here you can update your info, check your stats, your answered questions, and more!
                  </div>
                  <a href="http://arima.io/profile"><div class="button"><strong> Go!</strong></div></a>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr><td style="font-size: 0; line-height: 0;" height="20">&nbsp;</td></tr>
            </table>
          </td>
        </tr>
          <tr><td style="font-size: 0; line-height: 0;" height="1" bgcolor="#F9F9F9">&nbsp;</td></tr>
          <table border ="0" cellpadding = "0" align= "center" width = "55%">
          <tr>
            <td style="padding:10px 10px 20px 10px;">
              <div>
                Share your reports and tell your friends. Follow us on Twitter at @arima.io, and on Facebook at Arima!
                <br/><br/> Thanks for joining, and have fun!<br/><br/> The Arima Team
              </div>
            </td>
          </tr>
      </table>
    </table>     

  </body>
</html>